#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:-1
msgid ""
"Learn about the Maven build system in Spack for building and managing Java-"
"based projects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:13
msgid "Maven"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:15
msgid ""
"Apache Maven is a general-purpose build system that does not rely on "
"Makefiles to build software. It is designed for building and managing Java-"
"based projects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:19
msgid "Phases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:21
msgid ""
"The ``MavenBuilder`` and ``MavenPackage`` base classes come with the "
"following phases:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:23
msgid "``build`` - compile code and package into a JAR file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:24
msgid "``install`` - copy to installation prefix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:26
msgid "By default, these phases run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:28
msgid ""
"$ mvn package\n"
"$ install . <prefix>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:35
msgid "Important files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:37
msgid ""
"Maven packages can be identified by the presence of a ``pom.xml`` file. This "
"file lists dependencies and other metadata about the project. There may also "
"be configuration files in the ``.mvn`` directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:42
msgid "Build system dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:44
msgid ""
"Maven requires the ``mvn`` executable to build the project. It also requires "
"Java at both build- and run-time. Because of this, the base class "
"automatically adds the following dependencies:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:48
msgid ""
"depends_on(\"java\", type=(\"build\", \"run\"))\n"
"depends_on(\"maven\", type=\"build\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:54
msgid "In the ``pom.xml`` file, you may see sections like:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:56
msgid ""
"<requireJavaVersion>\n"
"   <version>[1.7,)</version>\n"
"</requireJavaVersion>\n"
"<requireMavenVersion>\n"
"   <version>[3.5.4,)</version>\n"
"</requireMavenVersion>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:66
msgid ""
"This specifies the versions of Java and Maven that are required to build the "
"package. See https://docs.oracle.com/middleware/1212/core/MAVEN/"
"maven_version.htm#MAVEN402 for a description of this version range syntax. "
"In this case, you should add:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:70
msgid ""
"depends_on(\"java@7:\", type=\"build\")\n"
"depends_on(\"maven@3.5.4:\", type=\"build\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:77
msgid "Passing arguments to the build phase"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:79
msgid ""
"The default build and install phases should be sufficient to install most "
"packages. However, you may want to pass additional flags to the build phase. "
"For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:83
msgid ""
"def build_args(self):\n"
"    return [\"-Pdist,native\", \"-Dtar\", \"-Dmaven.javadoc.skip=true\"]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:90
msgid "External documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mavenpackage.rst:92
msgid ""
"For more information on the Maven build system, see: https://maven.apache."
"org/index.html"
msgstr ""
